Apologies, this was a change in the dependency. This was resolved by inlining the definition. We need PNat here to reuse the `HasAntidiagonal` code which doesn't play nice with 0.
I think this one doesn't need to be private. It could also be moved above the `def f`.

I'm inclined to suggest that you wrap the private decls above in a namespace `card_pair_lcm_eq`. This isn't really for technical reasons, but just for psychological benefits.
